"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-05-paris-2024-olympics-ofili-reaches-womens-200m-final\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Favour Ofili has qualified for the final of the women's 200m at the 2024 Olympic Games.  Ofili executed a good race plan to grab the second automatic spot in the second semi-final.  The 21-year-old finished second with a season's best of 22.05s.  Saint Lucia's Julien Alfred won the race crossing the line in a time of 21.98s.  McKenzie Long of the United States of America came in third in a time of 22.30s.  Ofili is the first Nigerian woman to qualify for the final of the 200m at the Olympics in 28 years.  Mary Onyali made it to the final of the women's 200m at the Atlanta 1996 games.  She won bronze medal in the event.  EPL: Man Utd new signing Yoro undergoes surgery, out for three months  Transfer: He refuses to reduce his salary - Romano updates on Chelsea's move for Osimhen  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"